(iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg - Twenty-two high school pupils and three adults were taken to hospital in Vereeniging, Gauteng, after a swarm of bees attacked them on Thursday morning.ER24 spokesperson Chitra Bodasing Harduth said a beehive was disturbed at the school while maintenance workers were apparently cutting grass."All patients are in a stable condition at this stage," she said."There are instances where you cannot foresee bee attacks. General advice to the public would be not to provoke bees or interfere with bee hives. Seek professional assistance." 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.